         <h4>What is pair programming?</h4>
          <p>Pair programming is where two programmers work together on a program with one person as a driver and the other a navigator.</p></div>

       <div id="box2" class="box">
         <h4>Why is pair programming important?</h4>
         <p>It is important working in pairs to have someone collaborating and checking your work.</p></div>

       <div id="box3" class="box">
         <h4>Compare driver and navigator?</h4>
          <p>Driver writes the code while the navigator directs what the driver should be focusing on. Its a give and take relationship!</p></div>

